FEATURE_007 built. The form now POSTs to `src/app/api/leads/route.ts`, a server-only route handler that validates name/email, instantiates Supabase from `SUPABASE_URL` + `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` (server-side only, never sent to the browser), and inserts into the `leads` table defined in `supabase/schema.sql`. The form surfaces a clear error message on failure and keeps the existing success state on insert. `npm run build` passes; report at `.ai-build/last_build_report.md`.

To go live: run the SQL in a Supabase project and set the two env vars in the deployment environment.


